Target: OntoSewage is an ontology developed for representing sewerage system.

Comment: is the infrastructure that conveys sewage or surface runoff (stormwater, meltwater, rainwater) using sewers.
Label: Sewerage component

Comment: is a conglomeration of pipes and sewers that work together to collect and drain wastewater from the population or industrial centers to off-site treatment facilities.
Label: Sewerage network

Comment: contains branch pipes
Label: Sub network

Comment: contains main pipes
Label: Main network

Comment: representing for what the sewerage is used
Label: Sewerage usage

Comment: the records such as functional state, ID, and owner of a sewerage component
Label: Sewerage records

Comment: defines the type of ownership for sewerage component
Label: Ownership type

Comment: is the operational state for sewerage component, i.e., under construction
Label: Functional state

Comment: are the construction properties of a sewerage component such as construction year and materials used.
Label: Construction properties

Comment: a surface or shape exposed by making a straight cut through pipe, especially at right angles to an axis
Label: Cross section

Comment: is the external form of a Manhole's cover, flume, shaft, or cross section.
Label: Shape

Comment: is a type of wastewater that is produced by a community of people.
Label: Sewerage fluid

Comment: is the type of pipe such as venting.
Label: Pipe type

Comment: is the degree of sloping in a pipe.
Label: Inclination

Comment: are the connection properties of a pipe.
Label: Connection properties

Comment: is defined as the type of endpoint which is connected to a pipe.
Label: Endpoint type

Comment: means taking a tapping connection from a run pipe directly by making a hole in the run pipe or using an outlet fitting, which provides a connection of pipe for fluid to flow from a higher diameter to a lower diameter of the pipe.
Label: Branch connection

Comment: is the type of a manhole.
Label: Node type

Comment: is the type of the node connected to a manhole.
Label: Connection type

Comment: is a removable plate forming the lid over the opening of a manhole, an opening large enough for a person to pass through that is used as an access point for an underground vault or pipe.
Label: Cover

Comment: is the type of manhole's cover.
Label: Cover class

Comment: it is below the taper and leads down to the base of the manhole.
Label: Shaft

Comment: is a human-made channel for water, in the form of an open declined gravity chute whose walls are raised above the surrounding terrain.
Label: Flume

Comment: is the associated infrastructure of a location.
Label: Associated infrastructure

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and sewerage usage
Label: has usage

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and its records
Label: has sewerage records

Comment: A relationship between sewerage records and its functional state
Label: has functional state

Comment: A relationship between sewerage records and its ownership type
Label: has ownership type

Comment: A relationship between a sewerage component and its construction properties
Label: has construction properties

Comment: A relationship between construction properties of a sewerage component and its channel type
Label: has channel type

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and sewerage fluid
Label: used for

Comment: A relationship between a pipe type and pipe
Label: has pipe type

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and its cross section
Label: has cross section

Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and height
Label: has height

Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and width
Label: has width

Domain: CrossSection UNION Cover UNION Shaft UNION Flume
Comment: A relationship between a cross section of a pipe and shape
Label: has shape

Domain: http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Height UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Width UNION Inclination UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Length UNION  http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Thickness UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Distance UNION http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/Depth

Comment: A relationship between a measure and the respective unit of measure
A relationship between a pipe and inclination
Label: has inclination

Comment: A relationship between a pipe or a flume or a shaft and length
Label: has length

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and its wall thickness
Label: has wall thickness

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and connection properties
Label: has connection properties

Comment: A relationship between connection properties of a pipe and endpoint of the connection
Label: has endpoint type

Comment: A relationship between a branch connection and a pipe
Label: has branch pipe

Comment: A relationship between a branch connection and a pipe
Label: has main pipe

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and location (outlet)
Label: has outlet location

Comment: A relationship between a pipe and location (inlet)
Label: has inlet location

Comment: A relationship of distance between a branch connection and main pipe
Label: has distance from main pipe

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and cover
Label: has cover

Comment: A relationship between a cover and cover class
Label: has class

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and shaft
Label: has shaft

Comment: A relationship between a shaft and depth
Label: has depth

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and flume
Label: has flume

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and its type
Label: has node type

Comment: A relationship between a manhole and connection type
Label: has connection type

Comment: A relationship between a location and associated infrastructure
Label: is associated with

Comment: A relationship between a location and Geo coordinates
Label: has coordinates

Comment: A relationship between a location and elevation
Label: has elevation

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation above see level of a location
Label: has elevation above sea level

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation reference
Label: has elevation reference

Comment: A relationship which shows the elevation accuracy
Label: has elevation accuracy

Comment: sewerage component ID
Label: component ID

Comment: sewerage plant ID
Label: has sewage plant ID

Comment: construction year for a sewerage component
Label: construction year

Comment: connection ID of a pipe
Label: has connection ID

Comment: source ID of a pipe
Label: has source ID

Comment: is where the sewage enters a pipe
Label: has upstream connector

Comment: is where the sewage exits a pipe
Label: has downstream connector

Comment: endpoint object of a pipe
Label: has endpoint object

Comment: position of branch pipe
Label: clock position of branch pipe

Comment: defines whether relative distance on main pipe is measured in or against flow direction
Label: is in flow direction

Comment: tells whether the location is in water protection zone
Label: is in water protection zone

Comment: tell whether the location is in flood plane
Label: is in flood plane

Comment: catchment area key of a location
Label: has catchment area key

Comment: point designation of a location
Label: has point designation

Comment: district reference of a location
Label: has district reference

Comment: district name of a location
Label: has district name

Comment: street reference of a location
Label: has street reference

Comment: street name of a location
Label: has street name

Label: has position accuracy
